node.text:
It's the 77th anniversary of D-Day, where we reflect upon what was lost and what was gained during that fateful time in history. We all ought remember the sacrifices made and ask ourselves: how do we measure up to that? How do we make the efforts of those heroic men worth it?

@coffeeordiemag

node.text:
Today we remember those lost on that day:
U.S. Air Force Technical Sergeant John A. Chapman
⁣
Navy SEAL Petty Officer 1st Class Neil “Fifi” C. Roberts⁣
⁣
Air Force Pararescueman Senior Airman Jason D. Cunningham⁣
⁣
160th Special Operations Aviation Regiment (SOAR) Sergeant Philip “Spytech” Svitak⁣
⁣
Corporal Matthew A. Commons⁣
⁣
Sergeant Bradley S. Crose⁣
⁣
Specialist Marc A. Anderson⁣
Two Medals of Honor were awarded for actions taken that day, one to Air Force Combat Controller Tech. Sgt John A. Chapman (posthumously) and the other to Senior Chief Special Warfare Operator Britt K. Slabinski. Our guys at @coffeeordiemag had the distinct honor of speaking to one of the Rangers who fought on "Roberts Ridge" — check out the link in their bio (or head to our stories) to read the whole thing.

node.text:
Our crew at @coffeeordiemag just released the very first PRINT MAGAZINE! The Coffee or Die Magazine (like, actual physical magazine) is the culmination of some incredible work from the whole editorial staff, from the writers to the editors to the designers and everyone else who had a hand in making this a reality. We can't thank them enough for their hard work, and we certainly can't thank the readers enough for making this a legitimate reality.

If you want to get your hands on a copy, head to our site now before they're all gone!

It's not every day you come out with a first edition of a magazine. This one is chock full of original stories that can't be found anywhere else. We cover topics on the military and intel front, as well as first responders, history, entertainment, and of course... COFFEE. On top of all that, we've got comics, short stories, and poetry. There's definitely something for everyone, but our hearts go to the same audience we've always sought... people who love America, and in this case, people who love to read the stories near and dear to American hearts.

Cheers to everyone who had a hand in this. We can't wait to see all of the future editions to come (and yes, there will be more!).

@martyskovlundjr 
📷: @holtworks

Seeing service members enjoying our coffee NEVER gets old. A little caffeine goodness might not save the world, but we hope it makes life a little easier for the folks who put in the work every day for our country.

Swipe over to peep our latest LIBERTY ROAST, now available until July 11. Every purchase of Liberty Roast supports our Buy a Bag, Give a Bag goal of donating 1 MILLION CUPS of coffee to active military and first responders. These sorts of initiatives are only possible because of YOU, so THANK YOU for being an incredible group of people.

If you're interested in following our give-back programs and non-profit endeavors, head over to @brcc_gives to stay tuned.

Happy #fathersday to all the dads out there who put up with our sh*t on a daily basis. And an extra happy Father's Day to the dads like @brcc_ed who can dish it right back!

@evanhafer’s father Ed Hafer is the epitome of a hard-working father who sets the example for future generations to follow. He's the facilities manager in our Salt Lake City location, and he spends his days making sure that everything runs as smoothly as they possibly can. He's always been the beating heart of the company, a solid foundation that led the company to growth in the first place.
